verses.text: Save me, O God ; for the waters are come in unto \add my\add* soul. \q1

I sink in deep mire , where \add there is\add* no standing : I am come into deep waters , where the floods overflow me.\f + \fr 69.2 \ft deep mire: Heb. the mire of depth\f*\f + \fr 69.2 \ft deep waters: Heb. depth of waters\f* \q1
I am weary of my crying : my throat is dried : mine eyes fail while I wait for my God. \q1

They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of mine head : they that would destroy me, \add being\add* mine enemies wrongfully , are mighty : then I restored \add that\add* which I took not away. \q1
O God , thou knowest my foolishness ; and my sins are not hid from thee.\f + \fr 69.5 \ft sins: Heb. guiltiness\f* \q1
Let not them that wait on thee, O Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* of hosts , be ashamed for my sake: let not those that seek thee be confounded for my sake, O God of Israel. \q1
Because for thy sake I have borne reproach ; shame hath covered my face. \q1
I am become a stranger unto my brethren , and an alien unto my mother’s children. \q1
For the zeal of thine house hath eaten me up ; and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me. \q1
When I wept , \add and chastened\add* my soul with fasting , that was to my reproach. \q1
I made sackcloth also my garment ; and I became a proverb to them. \q1
They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I \add was\add* the song of the drunkards.\f + \fr 69.12 \ft drunkards: Heb. drinkers of strong drink\f* \b \q1

But as for me, my prayer \add is\add* unto thee, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add in\add* an acceptable time : O God , in the multitude of thy mercy hear me, in the truth of thy salvation. \q1
Deliver me out of the mire , and let me not sink : let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters. \q1
Let not the waterflood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up , and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me. \q1
Hear me, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; for thy lovingkindness \add is\add* good : turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies. \q1
And hide not thy face from thy servant ; for I am in trouble : hear me speedily.\f + \fr 69.17 \ft hear…: Heb. make haste to hear me\f* \q1
Draw nigh unto my soul , \add and\add* redeem it: deliver me because of mine enemies. \q1
Thou hast known my reproach , and my shame , and my dishonour : mine adversaries \add are\add* all before thee. \q1

Reproach hath broken my heart ; and I am full of heaviness : and I looked \add for some\add* to take pity , but \add there was\add* none; and for comforters , but I found none.\f + \fr 69.20 \ft to take…: Heb. to lament with me\f* \q1
They gave me also gall for my meat ; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink. \b \q1
Let their table become a snare before them: and \add that which should have been\add* for \add their\add* welfare , \add let it become\add* a trap. \q1
Let their eyes be darkened , that they see not; and make their loins continually to shake. \q1
Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them. \q1

Let their habitation be desolate ; \add and\add* let none dwell in their tents.\f + \fr 69.25 \ft their habitation: Heb. their palace\f*\f + \fr 69.25 \ft let none…: Heb. let there not be a dweller\f* \q1
For they persecute \add him\add* whom thou hast smitten ; and they talk to the grief of those whom thou hast wounded.\f + \fr 69.26 \ft those…: Heb. thy wounded\f* \q1
Add iniquity unto their iniquity : and let them not come into thy righteousness.\f + \fr 69.27 \ft iniquity unto…: or, punishment of iniquity, etc\f* \q1
Let them be blotted out of the book of the living , and not be written with the righteous. \q1
But I \add am\add* poor and sorrowful : let thy salvation , O God , set me up on high. \b \q1
I will praise the name of God with a song , and will magnify him with thanksgiving. \q1
\add This\add* also shall please the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* better than an ox \add or\add* bullock that hath horns and hoofs. \q1
The humble shall see \add this, and\add* be glad : and your heart shall live that seek God.\f + \fr 69.32 \ft humble: or, meek\f* \q1
For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* heareth the poor , and despiseth not his prisoners. \q1
Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas , and every thing that moveth therein.\f + \fr 69.34 \ft moveth: Heb. creepeth\f* \q1
For God will save Zion , and will build the cities of Judah : that they may dwell there, and have it in possession. \q1
The seed also of his servants shall inherit it: and they that love his name shall dwell therein.
